Kubernetes 


1. Kubernetes architecture
Explanation:
Kubernetes follows a master-worker architecture.
	· Control Plane (Master):
			o kube-apiserver: Exposes the Kubernetes API.
			o etcd: Stores all cluster data.
			o kube-scheduler: Assigns pods to nodes.
			o kube-controller-manager: Handles controllers like replication.
			o cloud-controller-manager: Manages cloud-specific control loops.
	· Node (Worker):
			o kubelet: Communicates with API server, runs containers.
			o kube-proxy: Maintains network rules.
			o Container Runtime: Docker/containerd/CRI-O.
 
